            "answer_text": "Considering the fact that the observation balloons usually had interlocking fields of fire with Maxim machineguns and air defense below, and were hard initially to put down without incendiary rounds, they were considered more difficult to take down earlier in the war despite have almost no maneuverability. (Up and down.) Also, in the case of the observation balloon, if you get shot down, it\u2019s going to be behind the enemy\u2019s lines or damn close to no man\u2019s lines or the front, as it\u2019ll always be behind enemy lines, unlike dog fights. ",
